#: ../../guides/cli.md:1
msgid "The `axiom` command line"
msgstr "La ligne de commande `axiom`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:3
msgid ""
"Installing `axiomai-engine` provides the `axiom` command (also reachable as "
"`python -m axiom.cli`). Run `axiom --help` or `axiom <command> --help` for "
"the authoritative usage; this page is the annotated tour."
msgstr ""
"Installer `axiomai-engine` fournit la commande `axiom` (aussi accessible via"
" `python -m axiom.cli`). Lancez `axiom --help` ou `axiom <commande> --help` "
"pour l'usage faisant foi ; cette page est la visite commentée."

#: ../../guides/cli.md:7
msgid ""
"Wherever a command takes a *universe* argument, it accepts a `.db` file, a "
"source folder (compiled on the fly when needed) or a `.axiom` archive."
msgstr ""
"Partout où une commande prend un argument *univers*, elle accepte un fichier"
" `.db`, un dossier source (compilé à la volée si besoin) ou une archive "
"`.axiom`."

#: ../../guides/cli.md:10
msgid "Playing"
msgstr "Jouer"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:12
msgid "`axiom play`"
msgstr "`axiom play`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:14
msgid "Play a universe interactively in the terminal:"
msgstr "Jouer un univers de façon interactive dans le terminal :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "Option"
msgstr "Option"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "Effect"
msgstr "Effet"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "`--save SAVE_ID`"
msgstr "`--save SAVE_ID`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "Resume an existing save."
msgstr "Reprendre une sauvegarde existante."

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "`--new`"
msgstr "`--new`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "Force a new game."
msgstr "Forcer une nouvelle partie."

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "`--name NAME`"
msgstr "`--name NOM`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "Player name for a new game (default `Hero`)."
msgstr "Nom du joueur pour une nouvelle partie (défaut `Hero`)."

#: ../../guides/cli.md
#, python-brace-format
msgid "`--difficulty {Normal,Hardcore,Companion}`"
msgstr "`--difficulty {Normal,Hardcore,Companion}`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "Game mode for a new game."
msgstr "Mode de jeu pour une nouvelle partie."

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "`--temperature F` / `--top-p F`"
msgstr "`--temperature F` / `--top-p F`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "LLM sampling settings."
msgstr "Réglages d'échantillonnage du LLM."

#: ../../guides/cli.md
#, python-brace-format
msgid "`--verbosity {short,balanced,talkative}`"
msgstr "`--verbosity {short,balanced,talkative}`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md
msgid "Narration length."
msgstr "Longueur de la narration."

#: ../../guides/cli.md:29
msgid "The universe path is also searched in `~/AxiomAI/universes/`."
msgstr "Le chemin de l'univers est aussi cherché dans `~/AxiomAI/universes/`."

#: ../../guides/cli.md:31
msgid "Authoring (Universe-as-Code)"
msgstr "Création (Universe-as-Code)"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:33
msgid "`axiom compile`"
msgstr "`axiom compile`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:35
msgid ""
"Compile a source tree into a `.db` cache (see [the format](universe-"
"format.md)):"
msgstr ""
"Compiler une arborescence source en cache `.db` (voir [le format](universe-"
"format.md)) :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:42
msgid "`axiom decompile`"
msgstr "`axiom decompile`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:44
msgid "The inverse — turn an existing `.db` universe into an editable text tree:"
msgstr ""
"L'inverse — transformer un univers `.db` existant en arborescence texte "
"éditable :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:50
msgid "`axiom dev`"
msgstr "`axiom dev`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:52
msgid ""
"Authoring loop: watch a source tree and hot-recompile on every change "
"(`--interval` sets the polling period, default 1 s; `--db` overrides the "
"target cache path):"
msgstr ""
"Boucle de création : surveiller une arborescence source et recompiler à "
"chaud à chaque changement (`--interval` règle la période de scrutation, "
"défaut 1 s ; `--db` remplace le chemin du cache cible) :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:60
msgid "`axiom pack` / `axiom import`"
msgstr "`axiom pack` / `axiom import`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:62
msgid "Share universes as single-file `.axiom` archives:"
msgstr "Partager des univers en archives `.axiom` mono-fichier :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:69
msgid "`axiom populate`"
msgstr "`axiom populate`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:71
msgid ""
"Generate universe content with the configured LLM. Repeat `-t` for several "
"targets among `meta`, `stats`, `entities`, `rules`, `events`, `lore`, `map`:"
msgstr ""
"Générer du contenu d'univers avec le LLM configuré. Répétez `-t` pour "
"plusieurs cibles parmi `meta`, `stats`, `entities`, `rules`, `events`, "
"`lore`, `map` :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:78
msgid ""
"Without `--text`, the generation is inferred from the existing lore. See "
"[Populating a universe](populate.md)."
msgstr ""
"Sans `--text`, la génération s'inspire du lore existant. Voir [Peupler un "
"univers](populate.md)."

#: ../../guides/cli.md:81
msgid "Saves"
msgstr "Sauvegardes"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:83
msgid ""
"All `save-*` commands operate on a universe and a save identifier. See "
"[Saves, rewind and sharing](saves.md) for the concepts."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les commandes `save-*` opèrent sur un univers et un identifiant de "
"sauvegarde. Voir [Sauvegardes, rewind et partage](saves.md) pour les "
"concepts."

#: ../../guides/cli.md:86
msgid "`axiom save-show`"
msgstr "`axiom save-show`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:88
msgid ""
"Inspect a save's state, optionally at a past point (`--turn N` or `--minute "
"M`):"
msgstr ""
"Inspecter l'état d'une sauvegarde, éventuellement à un point passé (`--turn "
"N` ou `--minute M`) :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:95
msgid "`axiom save-export` / `axiom save-import`"
msgstr "`axiom save-export` / `axiom save-import`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:97
msgid "Round-trip a save through an editable `save_state.toml`:"
msgstr "Faire l'aller-retour d'une sauvegarde via un `save_state.toml` éditable :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:104
msgid "`axiom save-fork`"
msgstr "`axiom save-fork`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:106
msgid ""
"Fork a save into a new one, truncating the journal at a point (`--turn` / "
"`--minute`) — an alternate timeline:"
msgstr ""
"Forker une sauvegarde en une nouvelle, avec le journal tronqué à un point "
"(`--turn` / `--minute`) — une chronologie alternative :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:113
msgid "`axiom save-edit`"
msgstr "`axiom save-edit`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:115
msgid ""
"Fix an existing save in place by applying a correction TOML (stat patches "
"under `[state.<entity_id>]`, plus `[[inventory]]` and `[[modifiers]]` "
"entries); `--turn` targets a past point:"
msgstr ""
"Corriger une sauvegarde existante en place en appliquant un TOML de "
"correction (patchs de stats sous `[state.<entity_id>]`, plus des entrées "
"`[[inventory]]` et `[[modifiers]]`) ; `--turn` vise un point passé :"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:123
msgid "`axiom save-pack` / `axiom save-unpack`"
msgstr "`axiom save-pack` / `axiom save-unpack`"

#: ../../guides/cli.md:125
msgid "Share a single save as a `.axiomsave` archive:"
msgstr "Partager une sauvegarde seule en archive `.axiomsave` :"

